        <dict>
            <key>WFWorkflowActionIdentifier</key>
            <string>is.workflow.actions.comment</string>
            <key>WFWorkflowActionParameters</key>
            <dict>
                <key>WFCommentActionText</key>
                <string>Live Context Sleep — reads last night's sleep from the Health app and hands the total to the Scriptable script "Live Context Bridge" for the Live Context widget.

What it does:
- Finds Sleep samples from about the last day.
- Adds up each sample's Duration into a running total.
- Converts the total into minutes.
- Builds a Dictionary with type set to sleep and minutes set to the total.
- Runs the Scriptable script in the background, with Run in App turned off.

Runs with no input and shows no interface.</string>
            </dict>
        </dict>
        <dict>
            <key>WFWorkflowActionIdentifier</key>
            <string>is.workflow.actions.comment</string>
            <key>WFWorkflowActionParameters</key>
            <dict>
                <key>WFCommentActionText</key>
                <string>Shortcuts generated by Shortcuts Playground. May contain mistakes. Always check the shortcut's actions first.

This shortcut was created via the following user prompt:

&gt; Build an iOS shortcut named "Live Context Sleep" that reads last night's sleep from Health (Find Health Samples: Sleep Analysis where value is Asleep, last 24 hours), sums the durations in minutes into a single number, builds a Dictionary with "type" = "sleep" and "minutes" = that number, then uses the Scriptable "Run Script" action to run "Live Context Bridge" with that dictionary as input and Run in App disabled so it runs in the background. No input, no UI.</string>
            </dict>
        </dict>
